# .anonymity-patterns — patterns the anonymity guard will refuse to commit.
#
# Copy this file to `.anonymity-patterns` (which is gitignored) and edit with
# the actual names you want to block. Keeping the live file out of git ensures
# the public repo doesn't reveal which private project the guard is protecting.
#
# Format:
#   - One regex per line.
#   - Prefix `i:` for case-insensitive matching.
#   - Lines starting with `#` are comments.
#   - Blank lines are ignored.
#
# Tips:
#   - Use `\b` word boundaries for short acronyms — case-sensitive without `\b`
#     will false-positive on common substrings (e.g. "cov" matches "discover").
#   - Full project names are safe to match case-insensitively; they rarely
#     collide with anything benign.

# Example patterns — REPLACE THESE with your actual names:
\bExampleAcronym\b
i:example full project name
i:\bexample_package_slug\b
